Sec. 164.086. FAILURE TO DISINFECT SHEARING PLANT. (a) A
person commits an offense if the person fails or refuses to disinfect
all or part of a shearing plant, or the wearing apparel of each
person shearing the sheep or handling or packing the wool, in
accordance with Section 164.045 of this code.
(b) An offense under this section is a Class B misdemeanor.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1427, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 836, Sec. 48, eff. Sept. 1,
1989.

